Issues.Body:
### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

@angular/router@>=16.2.5

### Description

Hello,

My library to make routes translatable doesn't work anymore from 16.2.5.
I can see now `_loadedRoutes` is populate on lazyloading. Before it was populated on Initializer.

I totally understand the change but this change will create a feature request:
We can use `router.resetConfig(routes)` in "root" Router but can you make this function run for child routes ?
So `router.resetConfig(lazyloadedRoutes)` into lazyloaded module has to update only its routes not global routes.
In the same way `router.config` need to return only routes from lazyloaded module and not the entire config.

### Proposed solution

## State
Module 1 contains routes:
```
[
  {
      path: '',
      component: HomeComponent
  },
  {
     path: 'two',
     loadChildren: import(./my.module.ts).then(m => m.MyModule)
  }
]
```
Module 2 contains routes:
```
[
  {
      path: '',
      component: ComponentTwo
  },
  {
     path: 'three',
     component: ComponentThree
  }
]
```
## Expectation
### config
Expected return of `router.config` into AppModule:
```
[
  {
      path: '',
      component: HomeComponent
  },
  {
     path: 'two',
     loadChildren: import(./my.module.ts).then(m => m.MyModule)
  }
]
```
Expected return of `router.config` into MyModule
```
[
  {
      path: '',
      component: ComponentTwo
  },
  {
     path: 'three',
     component: ComponentThree
  }
]
```
### config
Reset config into AppModule:
```
router.resetConfig([
  {
      path: '',
      component: HomeComponent
  },
  {
     path: 'two',
     loadChildren: import(./my.module.ts).then(m => m.MyModule)
  }
])
```
Reset config into MyModule:
```
router.resetConfig([
  {
      path: '',
      component: ComponentTwo
  },
  {
     path: 'three',
     component: ComponentThree
  }
])
```

### Alternatives considered

Create an other way to resetConfig of routes managed by a lazyloaded module
